[div class=p 
	"Uses PCem 17+st-1 with the Early 90s package, with the game placed onto a CD.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Main improvements come from doing "corner boosts" more (old movie did not do them in all possible places) and reducing the score counter (to reduce score countdown time at the end of a level).
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Game can officially be obtained here: 
	[a href=https://www.wieringsoftware.nl/mario/index.html rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"https://www.wieringsoftware.nl/mario/index.html
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Note: At a glance this movie appears slower than the linked publication, even after substracting the longer DOS terminal part. This is because of an 
	[a href=https://github.com/TASEmulators/pcem/issues/13 rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"inaccuracy in PCem
	]a
	", causing the internal refresh rate to be lower than expected. After taking that into account, this submission is faster than the linked publication.
	$LF
]div
